gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Pacers 122, Bucks 113
gameRecap.excerpt: The Pacers defeated the Bucks, 122-113. Tyrese Haliburton led the way for the Pacers with 26 points, nine rebounds, and 11 assists, while Bennedict Mathurin added 25 points and 13 rebounds in the victory. Giannis Antetokounmpo tallied 30 points, a season-high 18 rebounds, and 11 assists for the Bucks in the losing effort. This is Antetokounmpo's 3rd triple-double of the season, and 38th of his career. The Pacers are on a 4-game winning streak as they improve to 18-14 on the season, while the Bucks fall to 24-9.
